benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: PUT /1.0/kb/admin/healthcheck - Put the host back into rotation

covered: Successful PUT to put host back into rotation (TC01)
PUT request when host is already in rotation (TC02)
Forbidden access due to insufficient permissions (TC04)
PUT request with invalid HTTP method (TC06)
PUT request with additional unexpected headers (TC08)
PUT request with missing required headers (TC09)
PUT request during degraded system performance (TC10)
Regression - Previously fixed issue for host rotation (TC11)
PUT request with network interruption (transient failure) (TC13)
PUT request with large number of concurrent requests (TC14)
gaps: No tests explicitly cover the handling of non-empty request bodies with invalid data or malformed payloads.
No scenarios test the system response to race conditions or concurrent modifications beyond basic concurrency.
Lack of explicit tests for system behavior under high load or stress conditions beyond concurrency.
No tests for caching headers or validation of cache-related behavior.
recommendations: Add tests for invalid or malformed payloads in PUT requests to verify validation and error handling.
Include scenarios simulating race conditions or conflicting concurrent requests.
Implement stress testing scenarios to evaluate system behavior under high load.
Add tests to verify caching headers like ETag and Cache-Control for the endpoint.
